<br>
Pull mob, put pet on mob.  I prefer earth myself for the root, although some people will use Monster pets.<br>
<br>
Don't nuke.  You don't want the added aggro.  When you chain cast the 2nd pet, he will have zero aggro, and you will have a ton if you have been nuking.  This means mob runs after you for awhile and pet can't taunt it off.  Ok to do if you plan on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> reverse kiting</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but not ok if you are in close quarters.<br>
<br>
Once pet is getting close to dying, start summoning the new one.  This is where timing and practice pay off (and why earth pet root can help).  To be the most mana efficient, you want the 1st pet nearly dead when 2nd one is about to finish.<br>
<br>
While the spell is casting, type in /pet get lost, do NOT hit enter yet.  When the purple spell cast time line is just about finish, hit enter.  1st pet poofs, 2nd pet summons completes, you send 2nd pet at the mob.<br>
<br>
Rinse and repeat.  You can DS pet if you want to, it adds very little aggro to you.  Sit back down and med up for next pet if you can do it without mob running at you.  When mob gets down low enough, finish it off with a final nuke.<br>
<br>
It is one of the most mana efficient ways to solo, and sometimes the only way to kill certain mobs.  Shimmering rockfiends for example take way to much time/mana to nuke them down before 1st pet is dead.<br>
