- Watch out how fast your pet health is going down.  That will help indicate when to cast.  For some mobs I can start casting at 20% health, others its more like 30%.<br>
- Wear your focus ring which speeds up casting.  The extra second can allow you let your pet hang around for a few more hits.<br>
- If your pet doesn't listen to you when you say get lost (I saw that a few times) don't panic.  Just recast the pet, hope that your old one doesn't die and listens to you this time, or his root holds after he dies.  If all this fails, you'll get hit, interrupting your casting.  That's when you run.<br>
<br>
I didn't chain cast for a long time, but its very efficient.  With KEI and rods I have no downtime in the Grey.  Sure, I take longer to kill things, but I never have to med to recover.  I even have to nuke to get my mana down.  So once in a while I get a few quick kills.<br>
<br>
